-- UK's Saga first-half profit rises, names new CFO
-- By Richa Naidu in Bangalore
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 02:47AM EDT
-- None



Sept 30 (Reuters) - Saga Plc <SAGAG.L>, a British travel and insurance company that focuses on customers over 50, said first-half profit rose 14.9 percent as its travel insurance and private medical insurance units performed strongly.

The company also named Bovis Homes Group <BVS.L> Financial Director Jonathan Hill its new chief financial officer designate, saying its CFO of 14 years, Stuart Howard, would retire at the end of 2015. [ID:nRSd9315Sa] Saga, which was listed on the London Stock Exchange in May by its private equity owners Permira [PERM.UL], Charterhouse [CHCAP.UL] and CVC [CVC.UL], said it would meet full-year market expectations.